This paper deals with sequential pattern mining, which is a subfield of data mining and machine learning. The paper proposes a global constraint for mining sequential patterns with gap constraint, which involves designing efficient algorithms and data structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (databases), followed by cs.AI (artificial intelligence) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). The paper also involves experimental evaluations, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.DM (discrete mathematics).
